---
import TerminalWindow from '../../components/TerminalWindow.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<section id="install">
  <span class="doc-badge">Guide</span>
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p class="doc-lead">
    Install vulnex and run your first vulnerability query in under two minutes.
    No API keys required — vulnex works out of the box with public data sources.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>

  <h3>Homebrew (macOS / Linux)</h3>
  <TerminalWindow>
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">brew install anassahel/tap/vulnex</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>

  <h3>Go install</h3>
  <TerminalWindow>
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">go install github.com/trustin-tech/vulnex@latest</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>

  <h3>Binary download</h3>
  <p>
    Download the latest release from
    <a href="https://github.com/AnasSahel/vulnex/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Releases</a>
    for your platform (Linux, macOS, Windows).
  </p>

  <p>Verify the installation:</p>
  <TerminalWindow>
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex version</span>
<span class="t-value">vulnex v1.4.0</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>
</section>

<hr class="doc-divider" />

<section id="first-query">
  <h2>Your first query</h2>
  <p>Look up a CVE by ID — enriched with data from all sources by default:</p>
  <TerminalWindow title="vulnex cve get">
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2024-3094</span>

  <span class="t-cve"><strong>CVE-2024-3094</strong></span> — Malicious code in xz-utils
  <span class="t-label">Severity</span>            <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (10.0)</span>
  <span class="t-label">Priority</span>            <span class="t-p0">P0 — Critical: actively exploited, high EPSS</span>
  <span class="t-label">EPSS</span>                <span class="t-value">0.76460 (76.5%)</span> — percentile: 99.80%
  <span class="t-label">KEV</span>                 <span class="t-critical">Yes</span> — due 2024-04-19
  <span class="t-label">Published</span>           2024-03-29
  <span class="t-label">Sources</span>             <span class="t-green">NVD</span> · <span class="t-green">KEV</span> · <span class="t-green">EPSS</span> · <span class="t-green">GHSA</span> · <span class="t-green">OSV</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>
</section>

<hr class="doc-divider" />

<section id="cve-get">
  <h2>Enriching a CVE</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>cve get</code> command aggregates data from all five sources (NVD, KEV, EPSS, GHSA, OSV)
    and computes a risk priority score:
  </p>
  <TerminalWindow title="vulnex cve get">
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span>

  <span class="t-cve"><strong>CVE-2021-44228</strong></span> — Apache Log4j2 JNDI
  <span class="t-label">Severity</span>            <span class="t-critical">CRITICAL (10.0)</span>
  <span class="t-label">Priority</span>            <span class="t-p0">P0 — Critical: actively exploited, high EPSS</span>
  <span class="t-label">EPSS</span>                <span class="t-value">0.97185 (97.2%)</span> — percentile: 99.99%
  <span class="t-label">KEV</span>                 <span class="t-critical">Yes</span> — due 2021-12-24
  <span class="t-label">Sources</span>             <span class="t-green">NVD</span> · <span class="t-green">KEV</span> · <span class="t-green">EPSS</span> · <span class="t-green">GHSA</span> · <span class="t-green">OSV</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>
</section>

<hr class="doc-divider" />

<section id="output-formats">
  <h2>Output formats</h2>
  <p>Every command supports multiple output formats via <code>--output</code>:</p>

  <table class="doc-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Format</th><th>Flag</th><th>Use case</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Table</td><td><code>--output table</code></td><td>Human-readable (default)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>JSON</td><td><code>--output json</code></td><td>Scripting, pipelines</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CSV</td><td><code>--output csv</code></td><td>Spreadsheets, data analysis</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Markdown</td><td><code>--output markdown</code></td><td>Reports, GitHub issues</td></tr>
      <tr><td>YAML</td><td><code>--output yaml</code></td><td>Configuration integration</td></tr>
      <tr><td>SARIF</td><td><code>--output sarif</code></td><td>GitHub Code Scanning</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <TerminalWindow>
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex cve get</span> <span class="t-cve">CVE-2021-44228</span> <span class="t-flag">--output json</span> <span class="t-flag">| jq .priority</span>
<span class="t-value">"P0-CRITICAL"</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>
</section>

<hr class="doc-divider" />

<section id="scan">
  <h2>Scanning a lockfile</h2>
  <p>Point vulnex at any supported lockfile to find vulnerable dependencies:</p>
  <TerminalWindow title="vulnex sbom check">
    <pre><span class="t-prompt">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">vulnex sbom check</span> <span class="t-flag">go.sum</span>

<span class="t-dim">Scanning go.sum... found 142 packages</span>
<span class="t-dim">Querying OSV for vulnerabilities...</span>

<span class="t-label">PACKAGE</span>              <span class="t-label">VERSION</span>     <span class="t-label">CVE</span>                <span class="t-label">SEVERITY</span>
golang.org/x/net     v0.7.0      <span class="t-cve">CVE-2023-39325</span>     <span class="t-high">HIGH</span>
golang.org/x/crypto  v0.6.0      <span class="t-cve">CVE-2023-48795</span>     <span class="t-medium">MEDIUM</span>

<span class="t-dim">2 vulnerabilities found in 142 packages</span></pre>
  </TerminalWindow>

  <p>Supported lockfiles: <code>go.sum</code>, <code>package-lock.json</code>,
    <code>yarn.lock</code>, <code>pnpm-lock.yaml</code>, <code>Cargo.lock</code>,
    <code>Gemfile.lock</code>, <code>requirements.txt</code>, <code>poetry.lock</code>,
    <code>composer.lock</code>.</p>
</section>

<hr class="doc-divider" />

